  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'The Gut–Brain Axis: Why Digestion Shapes Your Mood' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (3.1ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'Your gut is often called your "second brain" — and for good reason. Millions of neurons line the digestive tract, in constant dialogue with the brain through the vagus nerve.

## The conversation
This two-way street means stress can upset digestion, and an inflamed gut can cloud mood and energy. Around 90% of the body''s serotonin — a key mood molecule — is produced in the gut.

## Nurturing the axis
Fiber-rich plants feed beneficial bacteria. Fermented foods add diversity. Slow, mindful eating signals safety to the nervous system. Even a short walk after meals supports motility.

## The holistic takeaway
When we care for the gut, we''re also caring for mood, focus and resilience. Track how meals make you feel in your chart — patterns reveal themselves quickly.', 'Gut Health', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.531151', '#4a7c59', '2026-05-30', 5, 'Your gut and brain are in constant conversation. Here''s how nurturing one nourishes the other.', NULL, 'The Gut–Brain Axis: Why Digestion Shapes Your Mood', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.531151') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.7ms)[0m  [1m[35mCOMMIT TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'Sea Moss: Nature''s Mineral-Rich Multivitamin' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (3.9ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'Sea moss (Chondrus crispus) is a red algae harvested from the ocean, traditionally used across the Caribbean and beyond.

## Why people love it
It''s naturally rich in minerals and trace elements, and its gel-like texture comes from carrageenan, a soluble fiber that can soothe the digestive tract.

## How to use it
A spoonful of gel blends easily into smoothies, teas or oatmeal. Start small and listen to your body.

## A balanced view
Sea moss is a supplement, not a miracle. It works best inside a varied, whole-food diet. As always, check with your clinician — especially regarding thyroid and iodine intake.', 'Sea Moss', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.546363', '#2d4a30', '2026-05-24', 4, 'Wildcrafted sea moss is prized for its minerals and gut-soothing properties. A grounded look.', NULL, 'Sea Moss: Nature''s Mineral-Rich Multivitamin', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.546363') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.3ms)[0m  [1m[35mCOMMIT TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'Strength Training Isn''t Just for the Gym' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.1ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (4.1ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'Muscle is metabolic gold. It burns energy at rest, stabilizes blood sugar and protects your bones and joints as you age.

## You don''t need a gym
Bodyweight squats, push-ups against a counter, and light dumbbells are enough to begin. Two to three short sessions a week create real change.

## Progress gently
The principle is simple: do a little more over time. Add a rep, slow the tempo, or reach for slightly heavier weights.

## Recovery is part of training
Muscle grows during rest. Sleep, protein and mobility days aren''t optional extras — they''re where the adaptation happens.', 'Movement', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.561555', '#a3b18a', '2026-06-02', 5, 'Building muscle protects metabolism, bones and independence — and you can start at home.', NULL, 'Strength Training Isn''t Just for the Gym', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.561555') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.5ms)[0m  [1m[35mCOMMIT TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.3ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'Sleep: The Most Underrated Wellness Tool' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.1ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (3.1ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'Sleep is when the body repairs tissue, consolidates memory and rebalances hormones that govern hunger and stress.

## Signs you need more
Afternoon energy crashes, sugar cravings and short temper often trace back to short or fragmented sleep.

## Build a wind-down
Dim the lights an hour before bed, keep screens away, and let the room run cool. A consistent sleep and wake time is more powerful than any gadget.

## Track it
Log your sleep hours in each check-in. Over a few weeks you''ll see how rest connects to mood, cravings and workout quality.', 'Sleep', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.575202', '#6b6b6b', '2026-05-27', 4, 'No supplement rivals a good night''s sleep. Small rituals make a big difference.', NULL, 'Sleep: The Most Underrated Wellness Tool', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.575202') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.7ms)[0m  [1m[35mCOMMIT TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.3ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'Mindful Eating: Slowing Down to Heal' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.1ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (4.8ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'Mindful eating is the practice of bringing full attention to your meals — and it''s one of the gentlest ways to improve digestion and your relationship with food.

## Why it works
Eating in a rushed, stressed state shifts the body into "fight or flight," which slows digestion. Slowing down activates "rest and digest."

## Simple practices
Put the fork down between bites. Notice color, texture and flavor. Pause halfway and ask how hungry you still are.

## The ripple effect
People who eat mindfully often naturally eat enough — no rigid rules required. Log meals in your chart to stay aware without obsessing.', 'Nutrition', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.587761', '#c9a96e', '2026-06-04', 4, 'How you eat matters as much as what you eat. Presence changes digestion.', NULL, 'Mindful Eating: Slowing Down to Heal', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.587761') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.7ms)[0m  [1m[35mCOMMIT TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Load (0.2ms)[0m  [1m[34mSELECT "articles".* FROM "articles" WHERE "articles"."title" = 'Breath & Stress: Your Built-In Reset Button' LIMIT 1 /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mTRANSACTION (0.1ms)[0m  [1m[35mBEGIN immediate TRANSACTION /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
  [1m[36mArticle Create (4.6ms)[0m  [1m[32mINSERT INTO "articles" ("author", "body", "category", "created_at", "hero_color", "published_on", "read_minutes", "summary", "tag", "title", "updated_at") VALUES ('Celine Bonilla, RN', 'When stress spikes, breathing becomes shallow and fast. The good news: you can reverse the signal consciously.

## The physiology
Slow, extended exhales stimulate the vagus nerve, nudging the body toward calm. This lowers heart rate and eases tension.

## Try this
Inhale for a count of four, exhale for a count of six. Repeat for two minutes. That''s it.

## Make it a habit
Pair breathwork with your evening check-in. Watch your stress scores soften over time — proof that small practices compound.', 'Mindfulness', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.603121', '#4a7c59', '2026-05-21', 3, 'A few minutes of slow breathing can shift your whole nervous system.', NULL, 'Breath & Stress: Your Built-In Reset Button', '2026-06-05 21:54:11.603121') RETURNING "id" /*application='HolisticChart'*/[0m
